1
00:00:00,001 --> 00:00:08,001
( Watch on www.kissasia.co, .club, .be, .org, .net, .id, .xyz )

2
00:00:08,185 --> 00:00:10,725
(Lee Na Young)

3
00:00:16,525 --> 00:00:19,325
(Jung Eun Chae)

4
00:00:20,965 --> 00:00:23,505
(Lee Chung Ah)

5
00:00:31,005 --> 00:00:35,045
(Honour)

6
00:00:35,715 --> 00:00:38,245
(Supported by the Culture Ministry and Korea's Creative Content Agency)

7
00:00:39,015 --> 00:00:40,015
(All people, incidents, and backgrounds...)

8
00:00:40,085 --> 00:00:41,185
(in this drama are fictitious and unrelated to reality.)

9
00:00:41,685 --> 00:00:42,755
(Also, children and animals were filmed under production guidelines.)

10
00:01:06,605 --> 00:01:08,145
We have only one goal.

11
00:01:09,345 --> 00:01:11,485
To connect. To bring people together.

12
00:01:20,725 --> 00:01:23,155
Our real fight begins now.

13
00:01:25,765 --> 00:01:29,235
If you're watching this right now, please reach out to us.

14
00:01:30,465 --> 00:01:31,465
We will...

15
00:01:32,365 --> 00:01:33,365
take your hand.

16
00:01:37,575 --> 00:01:39,245
(Episode 4)

17
00:02:08,935 --> 00:02:10,505
I think someone's hurt.

18
00:02:11,105 --> 00:02:12,745
I heard a scream.

19
00:02:13,715 --> 00:02:16,985
It's a house in front of the park on Seongil-gu, Jungam-ro.

20
00:02:18,445 --> 00:02:21,415
The day Lee Jun Hyeok died, Hyun Jin was here.

21
00:02:25,185 --> 00:02:26,555
Was that her first time?

22
00:02:28,425 --> 00:02:29,725
Why did she come here?

23
00:02:33,395 --> 00:02:36,095
(Seoul Han Hospital)

24
00:02:39,135 --> 00:02:41,135
Wake up. You're late.

25
00:02:47,215 --> 00:02:49,875
Is that any way to talk to a friend who almost died?

26
00:02:50,415 --> 00:02:51,645
That's harsh.

27
00:02:52,215 --> 00:02:53,585
Are you with us? Feeling okay?

28
00:02:53,855 --> 00:02:55,215
Not at all.

29
00:02:55,885 --> 00:02:57,055
This is so unfair.

30
00:02:57,525 --> 00:03:00,055
If it had been one-on-one, I totally would've won.

31
00:03:00,395 --> 00:03:02,595
Gosh, this is so embarrassing.

32
00:03:03,155 --> 00:03:04,165
Looks like she's fine.

33
00:03:05,925 --> 00:03:07,165
What exactly happened?

34
00:03:07,495 --> 00:03:09,895
Witnesses said you just collapsed in front of the station.

35
00:03:10,295 --> 00:03:12,034
What do you mean, "just collapsed"?

36
00:03:12,035 --> 00:03:14,175
Hey, some jerk...

37
00:03:14,775 --> 00:03:16,575
stabbed me from behind and took off.

38
00:03:21,375 --> 00:03:22,375
Look at this.

39
00:03:28,185 --> 00:03:29,785
That jerk must have stamped this on me.

40
00:03:30,525 --> 00:03:31,555
The jerk who stabbed me.

41
00:03:39,865 --> 00:03:41,195
Yes, what about the subway's CCTV footage?

42
00:03:43,235 --> 00:03:45,465
Got it. I'll head over as soon as I check on my wife.

43
00:03:49,205 --> 00:03:51,545
My car and that stamp.

44
00:03:52,675 --> 00:03:53,715
What about the dashcam?

45
00:03:55,115 --> 00:03:57,845
They took the memory card. The CCTVs don't cover that spot.

46
00:04:01,155 --> 00:04:02,355
Remember that wine?

47
00:04:03,355 --> 00:04:06,685
- The one for our anniversary. - A 2005 vintage?

48
00:04:07,125 --> 00:04:09,195
It must've been from the alumni association.

49
00:04:09,625 --> 00:04:11,165
Then maybe that was also...

50
00:04:14,595 --> 00:04:15,595
This is a warning.

51
00:04:17,105 --> 00:04:18,505
A warning that they know what happened.

52
00:04:19,565 --> 00:04:21,375
Who on earth?

53
00:04:23,675 --> 00:04:24,675
Hyun Jin.

54
00:04:26,475 --> 00:04:27,475
Are you all right?

55
00:04:28,745 --> 00:04:30,915
- I'm sorry about yesterday... - Don't worry about it.

56
00:04:31,345 --> 00:04:33,145
It comes with being married to a detective.

57
00:04:33,755 --> 00:04:35,285
Really, I'm totally fine.

58
00:04:35,615 --> 00:04:37,325
Did the tox screen results come back?

59
00:04:38,025 --> 00:04:39,155
They found traces of heroin.

60
00:04:39,725 --> 00:04:40,725
Heroin?

61
00:04:40,895 --> 00:04:44,525
Luckily, it was just a trace amount. Any more would have been dangerous.

62
00:04:47,135 --> 00:04:50,865
Does anyone come to mind? Like someone who holds a grudge.

63
00:04:53,365 --> 00:04:54,375
Not really.

64
00:04:58,205 --> 00:05:00,815
Maybe it was just a random attack or something?

65
00:05:03,345 --> 00:05:04,345
With heroin?

66
00:05:07,355 --> 00:05:09,355
Have the police secured the CCTV footage?

67
00:05:09,685 --> 00:05:11,125
We'd like to review it as well.

68
00:05:12,225 --> 00:05:15,255
Yes, the detective is my junior. I was heading over there anyway.

69
00:05:17,225 --> 00:05:19,995
And yesterday, on the back of your hand...

70
00:05:24,035 --> 00:05:25,035
The back of my hand?

71
00:05:28,375 --> 00:05:31,275
Let's get you checked out first. I'll go talk to the nurse's station.

72
00:06:00,975 --> 00:06:01,975
Wait. About Hyun Jin.

73
00:06:03,005 --> 00:06:06,205
By any chance, before Reporter Lee Jun Hyeok died,

74
00:06:06,875 --> 00:06:08,175
did she ever meet with him privately?

75
00:06:10,075 --> 00:06:11,115
Why are you asking me that?

76
00:06:11,815 --> 00:06:13,785
Because you're the ones who know Hyun Jin best.

77
00:06:14,385 --> 00:06:16,155
You and Ra Young.

78
00:06:16,655 --> 00:06:17,755
Maybe even more than I do.

79
00:06:21,095 --> 00:06:22,995
It's funny how people can be so fickle.

80
00:06:23,965 --> 00:06:27,465
Just now, you were a nervous wreck, worried she wouldn't make it.

81
00:06:27,935 --> 00:06:30,735
It seemed like all you wanted was for Hyun Jin to wake up,

82
00:06:31,005 --> 00:06:33,565
but now that she is, that feeling's vanished, hasn't it?

83
00:06:34,635 --> 00:06:37,675
Would you still be asking me this if Hyun Jin hadn't made it?

84
00:06:41,775 --> 00:06:43,215
Yes, they met.

85
00:06:43,845 --> 00:06:44,945
She was requesting files for a story.

86
00:06:55,395 --> 00:06:57,125
- Delivery! - Hold on, one second!

87
00:06:57,195 --> 00:06:58,725
- Seriously, what should we do? - This is insane.

88
00:06:58,795 --> 00:06:59,795
What is this?

89
00:06:59,865 --> 00:07:02,165
I'm telling you, we didn't place this order.

90
00:07:02,665 --> 00:07:04,035
Why should we pay for something we didn't order?

91
00:07:04,105 --> 00:07:07,065
It's an order for 20 lunch boxes. So how are we getting paid?

92
00:07:07,335 --> 00:07:08,335
What's all this?

93
00:07:08,405 --> 00:07:10,535
Someone's bombarding us with malicious prank orders.

94
00:07:11,305 --> 00:07:13,975
Isn't this the kind of thing phishing scammers do for revenge?

95
00:07:14,875 --> 00:07:16,875
Every time we air a story, we get flooded with these "gifts."

96
00:07:17,585 --> 00:07:19,415
Pay for all the deliveries.

97
00:07:20,185 --> 00:07:21,285
What are you going to do with all this?

98
00:07:21,555 --> 00:07:24,155
If we send it all back, what will the restaurant owners do?

99
00:07:24,485 --> 00:07:25,485
We'll buy everything...

100
00:07:25,785 --> 00:07:28,695
and donate it to the nearby shelters and homeless outreach centers.

101
00:07:29,155 --> 00:07:32,065
Let's run a few stories on this. That'll buzz off whoever did this.

102
00:07:33,065 --> 00:07:36,495
- Understood. - Has anyone been looking for me?

103
00:07:36,765 --> 00:07:39,865
No. You have no meetings today.

104
00:07:40,405 --> 00:07:42,105
Someone named Han Min Seo should be coming soon.

105
00:07:42,435 --> 00:07:43,575
Bring her straight to me.

106
00:08:36,325 --> 00:08:38,425
You've been staring at the same page for 20 minutes.

107
00:08:39,895 --> 00:08:42,165
Here, have one. I set a few aside for us.

108
00:08:43,535 --> 00:08:44,705
Can you believe this?

109
00:08:45,165 --> 00:08:46,735
Not a single person has tried to contact us.

110
00:08:49,775 --> 00:08:52,005
These guys have no class.

111
00:08:52,275 --> 00:08:54,675
If they were going to send them, they could've sent the best.

112
00:08:55,075 --> 00:08:59,485
Surely someone saw my show. One must want to quit Connect.

113
00:09:00,815 --> 00:09:02,855
I didn't stir up all that trouble just to get nonsense like this.

114
00:09:04,455 --> 00:09:06,355
Maybe that's just how scared they are.

115
00:09:06,655 --> 00:09:08,925
Those guys killed Reporter Lee and Jo Yoo Jeong.

116
00:09:09,295 --> 00:09:11,765
There's no way the women in there don't know what they're capable of.

117
00:09:12,765 --> 00:09:14,895
It won't be easy for them to actually come forward.

118
00:09:15,195 --> 00:09:16,595
That goes for Han Min Seo too.

119
00:09:19,505 --> 00:09:21,105
Where did you say Han Min Seo works again?

120
00:09:23,075 --> 00:09:24,405
If she's too scared to come to us,

121
00:09:25,475 --> 00:09:26,475
then I'll go to her.

122
00:09:31,085 --> 00:09:33,185
You still can't tell which fork goes where?

123
00:09:34,385 --> 00:09:37,215
Is it that hard to tell a wine glass from a water goblet?

124
00:09:38,025 --> 00:09:39,925
Did you even graduate high school? Feels more like grade school.

125
00:09:40,085 --> 00:09:41,155
But I wasn't the one who did it.

126
00:09:41,495 --> 00:09:43,995
- What? - I didn't set this table.

127
00:09:50,365 --> 00:09:51,365
And your shoes?

128
00:09:51,735 --> 00:09:53,205
Did someone else put those on for you too?

129
00:09:53,765 --> 00:09:55,735
You want another complaint about lowering our standards?

130
00:09:56,635 --> 00:09:58,005
Order up for table 12.

131
00:10:00,105 --> 00:10:01,745
Just go take their order.

132
00:10:12,055 --> 00:10:13,125
Are you ready to order?

133
00:10:14,925 --> 00:10:16,895
The camera doesn't do me justice, does it?

134
00:10:21,165 --> 00:10:22,395
It's a pleasure to meet you, Han Min Seo.

135
00:10:22,735 --> 00:10:23,735
I'm Yoon Ra Young.

136
00:10:26,605 --> 00:10:28,575
Why didn't you come? I've been waiting for you.

137
00:10:31,945 --> 00:10:34,675
- What do you think you're doing? - You could've at least called.

138
00:10:35,075 --> 00:10:36,415
Then I wouldn't have been so worried.

139
00:10:37,645 --> 00:10:39,345
- If you're not going to order... - I'll have the Course A.

140
00:10:39,945 --> 00:10:41,015
No wine.

141
00:10:52,095 --> 00:10:53,095
Han Min Seo!

142
00:10:55,565 --> 00:10:56,895
I said I would come to you.

143
00:10:57,335 --> 00:10:59,235
I didn't tell you to show up here like this.

144
00:10:59,305 --> 00:11:01,275
Why are you putting me in such a difficult position?

145
00:11:01,605 --> 00:11:02,605
I was worried about you.

146
00:11:03,205 --> 00:11:06,305
A place like that? Anything could've happened to you.

147
00:11:09,045 --> 00:11:10,315
You're hesitating, aren't you?

148
00:11:12,015 --> 00:11:13,085
Just come to us.

149
00:11:29,195 --> 00:11:30,295
I promise you.

150
00:11:31,205 --> 00:11:32,565
I'll put everything on the line,

151
00:11:34,435 --> 00:11:36,205
that I won't let you get hurt.

152
00:11:40,275 --> 00:11:42,875
What, do you think I'm some kind of charity case?

153
00:11:43,115 --> 00:11:45,415
There are only three pairs in Korea, and I bought one.

154
00:11:45,915 --> 00:11:47,585
I want to wear them on my show next week,

155
00:11:48,215 --> 00:11:49,585
so you'll have to come and return them to me.

156
00:12:00,225 --> 00:12:03,335
That table from earlier wasn't set by Han Min Seo.

157
00:12:03,935 --> 00:12:06,035
- Excuse me? - I'm Han Min Seo's lawyer.

158
00:12:06,365 --> 00:12:10,875
In 2019, the labor law was amended to prohibit workplace harassment.

159
00:12:11,145 --> 00:12:12,275
You might want to brush up on that.

160
00:12:12,705 --> 00:12:14,075
Public humiliation, and defamation of character.

161
00:12:14,475 --> 00:12:16,015
Unless you want to be buried in lawsuits.

162
00:12:31,995 --> 00:12:33,265
Are you sure you're okay?

163
00:12:33,665 --> 00:12:35,294
- What? - Weren't you supposed to stay...

164
00:12:35,295 --> 00:12:36,335
in the hospital for another day?

165
00:12:37,905 --> 00:12:39,705
The way I feel right now,

166
00:12:40,165 --> 00:12:43,935
I could set a marathon record. Do you want me to prove it?

167
00:12:44,605 --> 00:12:46,875
Just don't overdo it for the next few days.

168
00:12:46,945 --> 00:12:50,575
Goodness, all right. I get it.

169
00:12:54,415 --> 00:12:56,015
The day Reporter Lee Jun Hyeok died...

170
00:12:59,325 --> 00:13:00,855
You went to his house, didn't you?

171
00:13:06,525 --> 00:13:08,135
I think someone's hurt.

172
00:13:08,735 --> 00:13:10,265
I heard a scream.

173
00:13:11,335 --> 00:13:14,575
It's a house in front of the park on Seongil-gu, Jungam-ro.

174
00:13:23,715 --> 00:13:25,485
- Honey. - What I'm about to say...

175
00:13:25,845 --> 00:13:27,615
I'm going to forget everything after this moment.

176
00:13:27,955 --> 00:13:30,615
And I'll never speak of it again for as long as I live.

177
00:13:33,485 --> 00:13:36,095
You know that, right? If there's one thing about me,

178
00:13:36,395 --> 00:13:38,395
it's that I'm a man of my word.

179
00:13:40,265 --> 00:13:41,335
So please,

180
00:13:42,195 --> 00:13:43,195
just be honest with me.

181
00:13:45,905 --> 00:13:48,475
Why did you go to Reporter Lee's house?

182
00:14:04,185 --> 00:14:05,425
Jun Hyeok...

183
00:14:06,785 --> 00:14:08,525
was supposed to give me some files.

184
00:14:11,665 --> 00:14:12,795
That's why I went there.

185
00:14:13,825 --> 00:14:15,365
And that's where I found him.

186
00:14:17,435 --> 00:14:19,135
Jun Hyeok was dead.

187
00:14:21,205 --> 00:14:22,335
Is that really the whole story?

188
00:14:25,805 --> 00:14:27,175
Why didn't you tell me?

189
00:14:30,645 --> 00:14:31,915
You have to admit,

190
00:14:33,085 --> 00:14:34,755
the whole situation looked suspicious.

191
00:14:36,885 --> 00:14:38,855
But Ra Young and Shin Jae knew, didn't they?

192
00:14:39,355 --> 00:14:41,225
That you went to Reporter Lee's house that day.

193
00:14:42,825 --> 00:14:43,825
Yes.

194
00:14:47,665 --> 00:14:49,395
You and your friends...

195
00:14:50,195 --> 00:14:52,235
Your bond looked so perfect at first I was almost jealous.

196
00:14:53,135 --> 00:14:54,735
Like sisters, or even family.

197
00:14:55,135 --> 00:14:56,435
I wondered, "Are all women like this?"

198
00:14:56,735 --> 00:14:58,245
"Does a bond like this really exist?"

199
00:14:59,475 --> 00:15:00,545
But...

200
00:15:02,115 --> 00:15:03,115
the bond you have...

201
00:15:04,115 --> 00:15:05,315
is...

202
00:15:06,185 --> 00:15:07,185
different.

203
00:15:10,355 --> 00:15:14,025
Are you saying you're jealous of Ra Young and Shin Jae?

204
00:15:17,055 --> 00:15:19,665
Let's just drop it and go to sleep. I'm tired.

205
00:15:23,265 --> 00:15:25,735
Do you know what else gives me this same feeling?

206
00:15:28,905 --> 00:15:29,905
Accomplices.

207
00:15:32,475 --> 00:15:34,545
Their fates are bound together.

208
00:15:35,045 --> 00:15:36,275
If one of them goes down,

209
00:15:37,015 --> 00:15:39,385
the other is bound to go down with them.

210
00:15:40,845 --> 00:15:41,955
Is there really nothing else about you...

211
00:15:42,555 --> 00:15:45,025
that I should know?

212
00:16:06,075 --> 00:16:07,075
There isn't.

213
00:16:16,955 --> 00:16:17,955
This is a warning.

214
00:16:18,555 --> 00:16:19,985
A warning that they know about it.

215
00:16:44,545 --> 00:16:48,285
When you start taking photos, you just want to avoid backlighting.

216
00:16:48,585 --> 00:16:52,385
Since the subject's face and details get completely lost in shadow.

217
00:16:53,155 --> 00:16:56,495
But sometimes you have to use that backlighting to your advantage.

218
00:16:56,555 --> 00:16:59,565
It shows the true outline that's invisible in bright light.

219
00:16:59,765 --> 00:17:02,995
Letting you see the silhouette in perfect clarity.

220
00:17:05,135 --> 00:17:08,175
Sometimes, the truth is hiding just behind the light.

221
00:17:09,175 --> 00:17:11,845
Photography is about using every element in the environment...

222
00:17:12,145 --> 00:17:14,075
to capture the truth that lies just beneath the surface.

223
00:17:25,685 --> 00:17:26,685
Kang Shin Jae?

224
00:17:28,455 --> 00:17:30,725
It's been a while. Do you have a minute?

225
00:17:33,625 --> 00:17:34,635
Here.

226
00:17:42,335 --> 00:17:44,035
You've always been into photography.

227
00:17:44,605 --> 00:17:46,244
- And you're still at it. - They asked me...

228
00:17:46,245 --> 00:17:48,515
to advise the club. It's just a hobby.

229
00:17:49,475 --> 00:17:52,045
Anyway, what brings you to campus?

230
00:17:52,285 --> 00:17:54,555
I came to check on something.

231
00:17:55,585 --> 00:17:58,025
We received a gift at our law firm's anniversary party,

232
00:17:58,685 --> 00:18:01,025
and I thought it might have been from the alumni association.

233
00:18:01,955 --> 00:18:02,955
A gift?

234
00:18:03,395 --> 00:18:06,925
- What was it? - Wine. A 2005 vintage.

235
00:18:08,065 --> 00:18:10,295
From 2005?

236
00:18:10,895 --> 00:18:13,835
Yes. That's the year we were all here at school,

237
00:18:13,905 --> 00:18:14,905
so I thought there might be a link.

238
00:18:15,705 --> 00:18:18,575
Right. So what did the alumni association say?

239
00:18:19,245 --> 00:18:20,245
That they didn't send it.

240
00:18:25,085 --> 00:18:26,685
This came with it too.

241
00:18:32,885 --> 00:18:34,425
This was one of your photos, right?

242
00:18:36,625 --> 00:18:37,855
I remember this.

243
00:18:38,625 --> 00:18:39,765
This was from the mock trial, wasn't it?

244
00:18:40,825 --> 00:18:42,935
Who would send this card to us?

245
00:18:43,735 --> 00:18:45,865
Do you have any idea who it might be?

246
00:18:46,765 --> 00:18:47,765
Hard to say.

247
00:18:49,405 --> 00:18:50,405
But...

248
00:18:50,835 --> 00:18:53,005
is there a particular reason you need to find the sender?

249
00:18:53,405 --> 00:18:56,075
It all just seems like a coincidence to me.

250
00:18:56,615 --> 00:18:58,445
The wine probably doesn't mean anything.

251
00:18:58,845 --> 00:19:01,555
And as for the photo, it was in the law school newsletter,

252
00:19:01,955 --> 00:19:04,385
so anyone could have found it if they really wanted to.

253
00:19:05,355 --> 00:19:06,355
You think so?

254
00:19:08,555 --> 00:19:11,595
How's everyone else doing? I see Ra Young on TV all the time.

255
00:19:12,425 --> 00:19:14,365
And I heard Hyun Jin got married a few years ago.

256
00:19:14,895 --> 00:19:16,695
Her husband's a detective, right?

257
00:19:17,335 --> 00:19:18,465
You're pretty up-to-date.

258
00:19:21,475 --> 00:19:22,475
They're all doing fine.

259
00:19:23,135 --> 00:19:24,135
I'll tell them you said hi.

260
00:19:29,615 --> 00:19:30,645
Professor.

261
00:19:31,215 --> 00:19:32,815
About that assignment you mentioned last time.

262
00:19:32,885 --> 00:19:34,045
Can we change our group members?

263
00:19:34,115 --> 00:19:36,284
No! I told you I can't change the groups for you!

264
00:19:36,285 --> 00:19:37,314
No! Go on.

265
00:19:37,315 --> 00:19:39,285
- Figure it out yourselves. - But, Professor...

266
00:19:39,355 --> 00:19:41,455
- Why do they keep telling me that? - There's someone who can verify it.

267
00:19:42,095 --> 00:19:43,455
He's an associate professor at Hankuk University.

268
00:19:43,525 --> 00:19:44,965
His name is Nam Jong Min.

269
00:20:31,805 --> 00:20:32,875
That's the guy.

270
00:20:33,305 --> 00:20:34,575
The one in the green hoodie?

271
00:20:38,445 --> 00:20:41,285
- What is it? - That's the same guy from my house.

272
00:20:44,255 --> 00:20:47,025
Then the guy in the hoodie must've messed with my car.

273
00:20:47,785 --> 00:20:49,225
Who on earth is he?

274
00:20:49,655 --> 00:20:52,465
Someone with a grudge, who's terrorizing us...

275
00:20:52,825 --> 00:20:55,365
and would dig up the past just to blackmail us.

276
00:20:58,665 --> 00:20:59,765
What if it's Connect?

277
00:21:00,265 --> 00:21:01,365
Connect?

278
00:21:01,875 --> 00:21:02,905
Think about it.

279
00:21:03,605 --> 00:21:06,205
This all started when we started looking into Connect.

280
00:21:06,745 --> 00:21:09,145
When we found out that Connect was the one who killed Reporter Lee,

281
00:21:09,215 --> 00:21:13,445
- they came after me. - And when you declared war on air,

282
00:21:13,515 --> 00:21:17,355
they started playing that card for real by going after Hyun Jin.

283
00:21:17,615 --> 00:21:18,785
How would Connect even know about...

284
00:21:19,055 --> 00:21:20,555
what happened back then?

285
00:21:22,225 --> 00:21:23,895
I just came from seeing Nam Jong Min.

286
00:21:25,225 --> 00:21:27,365
- Jong Min? - Why him?

287
00:21:27,795 --> 00:21:28,835
Remember that day?

288
00:21:29,095 --> 00:21:31,295
I told you I thought I saw a camera flash.

289
00:21:31,365 --> 00:21:34,065
I thought you just imagined that.

290
00:21:36,705 --> 00:21:38,205
If that was Jong Min,

291
00:21:38,845 --> 00:21:40,675
he would've told the police back then.

292
00:21:41,675 --> 00:21:42,915
But something's bothering you, isn't it?

293
00:21:43,375 --> 00:21:46,945
It's been 20 years. People change, and so do circumstances.

294
00:21:48,155 --> 00:21:51,555
Anyway, I asked Do Jun to look into Nam Jong Min, so let's wait.

295
00:21:54,955 --> 00:21:56,225
You have a visitor.

296
00:21:59,665 --> 00:22:00,725
Min Seo.

297
00:22:02,335 --> 00:22:04,665
I came to return your shoes.

298
00:22:05,265 --> 00:22:07,005
Are you just here for the shoes? Or...

299
00:22:14,045 --> 00:22:15,415
(Connect In)

300
00:22:18,845 --> 00:22:19,985
I have some conditions.

301
00:22:20,385 --> 00:22:22,885
I won't go to the police, and I won't testify in court.

302
00:22:22,955 --> 00:22:26,085
Don't worry about that. We won't reveal your identity.

303
00:22:26,285 --> 00:22:27,285
One more thing.

304
00:22:29,555 --> 00:22:32,725
Of all of you, I want to stay with one of you.

305
00:22:36,565 --> 00:22:40,865
She can stay with me at my place. I promised I'd protect her.

306
00:22:41,205 --> 00:22:44,735
And to be honest, I'd feel better if she was close by too.

307
00:22:46,205 --> 00:22:47,905
This is about Jo Yoo Jeong, isn't it?

308
00:22:48,175 --> 00:22:50,915
Anyway, to us, Han Min Seo...

309
00:22:51,215 --> 00:22:55,915
is our only way into Connect. We have to give her what she wants.

310
00:22:56,015 --> 00:22:58,355
If Connect really is the one attacking us,

311
00:22:58,985 --> 00:22:59,985
then all the more reason.

312
00:23:04,695 --> 00:23:08,895
- In-home personal training. - So it poses as a training app.

313
00:23:09,095 --> 00:23:11,065
Gosh, talk about tight security.

314
00:23:13,735 --> 00:23:16,935
I only see the notification window. Is this it?

315
00:23:17,005 --> 00:23:19,475
My app is different from the one the VIPs use.

316
00:23:20,005 --> 00:23:24,075
When a VIP picks and books someone, I just get notified on this app.

317
00:23:28,515 --> 00:23:29,585
Like this.

318
00:23:31,885 --> 00:23:33,425
I got this one this morning.

319
00:23:33,885 --> 00:23:35,595
Do you know who runs it?

320
00:23:37,455 --> 00:23:38,795
There are managers.

321
00:23:39,165 --> 00:23:42,395
They sometimes come to the location. They're the only ones I've met,

322
00:23:42,735 --> 00:23:45,505
- but they only reach me on the app. - How do you get paid?

323
00:23:45,565 --> 00:23:48,935
In cash. I get it from a dead drop. The amount varies for each job.

324
00:23:49,305 --> 00:23:51,845
It depends on the options the VIPs want.

325
00:23:54,145 --> 00:23:57,315
Options? What kind of options, specifically?

326
00:24:14,695 --> 00:24:15,895
Things like this.

327
00:24:19,035 --> 00:24:21,235
These guys are a bunch of sick scums.

328
00:24:28,875 --> 00:24:32,445
If you refuse... I mean, if you try to leave Connect...

329
00:24:32,745 --> 00:24:34,685
Then what happens?

330
00:24:35,315 --> 00:24:36,515
I'm about to find out.

331
00:24:37,255 --> 00:24:38,255
Now.

332
00:24:42,625 --> 00:24:45,765
I heard the three of you at the firm went to college together.

333
00:24:45,825 --> 00:24:50,795
I'm curious how you all decided to start a firm helping victims.

334
00:24:50,865 --> 00:24:54,604
We wanted victims to know we'd fight for them, not the perpetrators.

335
00:24:54,605 --> 00:24:56,905
We knew we had to get that message out there.

336
00:25:09,085 --> 00:25:11,315
(Connect In)

337
00:25:13,125 --> 00:25:15,055
(Prosecutor Park Je Yeol)

338
00:25:20,765 --> 00:25:23,165
(Biometric)

339
00:25:23,235 --> 00:25:25,105
(Select trainer)

340
00:25:25,165 --> 00:25:28,405
(DU19: Contact lost. Suspected contact with LnJ)

341
00:25:43,555 --> 00:25:45,225
("Hankuk University Law Student Sissing")

342
00:25:45,825 --> 00:25:48,355
(Investigation at a Standstill")

343
00:25:48,425 --> 00:25:50,895
("Male Hankuk University Student Missing for 48 Hours")

344
00:25:52,125 --> 00:25:54,695
("Hankuk University Law Student Gone, Where is He?")

345
00:26:06,175 --> 00:26:09,645
Gosh, this app is just a shell. I can't find anything on it.

346
00:26:09,875 --> 00:26:11,645
It's basically just a scheduling app.

347
00:26:11,815 --> 00:26:14,285
Can't you trace the server or something?

348
00:26:14,345 --> 00:26:16,555
You said this app's different from the one the users have, right?

349
00:26:17,385 --> 00:26:18,385
Yes.

350
00:26:18,625 --> 00:26:21,185
Then it's possible they connect to a different server altogether.

351
00:26:21,625 --> 00:26:24,295
If they made a separate app to avoid the risk of exposure,

352
00:26:24,355 --> 00:26:27,095
that means they're serious about security.

353
00:26:27,165 --> 00:26:29,765
So the users aren't just your average Joes.

354
00:26:29,835 --> 00:26:33,905
Exactly. Which means the real data probably isn't on this server.

355
00:26:33,965 --> 00:26:37,035
They've rerouted the connection like crazy.

356
00:26:37,105 --> 00:26:40,375
So what now? We can't trace their bank accounts.

357
00:26:40,445 --> 00:26:43,115
If we had the app for the clients, that'd be a different story.

358
00:26:43,175 --> 00:26:44,245
The client app?

359
00:26:44,315 --> 00:26:46,685
That app's the key. The code will be different,

360
00:26:46,745 --> 00:26:49,855
so we'd have to trace where the data is being sent.

361
00:26:52,925 --> 00:26:57,355
Do you remember any of the users? A name, an occupation, anything?

362
00:26:57,425 --> 00:27:00,865
I don't know any of them by name. I'd recognize their faces, though.

363
00:27:00,995 --> 00:27:04,295
- What about the locations? - It was mostly at hotels.

364
00:27:04,365 --> 00:27:07,105
If we check the guest registration, we might find their info, right?

365
00:27:07,165 --> 00:27:10,375
They make reservations in our names in case they're traced.

366
00:27:10,635 --> 00:27:14,245
Sometimes it wasn't at a hotel. Then Connect would drive us there,

367
00:27:14,305 --> 00:27:15,615
so we had no way of knowing the location.

368
00:27:15,975 --> 00:27:19,115
A separate crew cleans up after, so there's no evidence left.

369
00:27:20,845 --> 00:27:25,525
(Haeil Law Firm)

370
00:27:27,555 --> 00:27:28,625
(Prime Smart City Project Internal Docs)

371
00:27:30,455 --> 00:27:31,525
("Tech Must Protect the Weak")

372
00:27:38,165 --> 00:27:40,165
(The Prime: Protecting the weak, A new, people-first philosophy)

373
00:27:41,905 --> 00:27:42,905
(A special message from CEO Baek Tae Ju)

374
00:27:42,975 --> 00:27:44,075
("Technology Must Protect Human Dignity")

375
00:27:44,135 --> 00:27:45,405
(I saw him speak. He was the best. I'm a fan now.)

376
00:27:45,475 --> 00:27:46,475
(All his interviews are epic.)

377
00:27:46,545 --> 00:27:47,875
(He's got charisma and the brains.)

378
00:27:55,685 --> 00:27:57,085
What brings you here at this hour?

379
00:27:57,815 --> 00:27:59,685
I left some documents behind.

380
00:28:07,195 --> 00:28:10,295
Americano with two spoons of milk. Your usual recipe.

381
00:28:11,035 --> 00:28:12,365
Not bad.

382
00:28:12,665 --> 00:28:15,675
You working at Haeil. I get to see you more often.

383
00:28:15,735 --> 00:28:17,775
That's the only perk of swinging by this place.

384
00:28:19,445 --> 00:28:23,515
By the way, have you met CEO Baek? What's he like?

385
00:28:24,645 --> 00:28:26,645
He's interesting.

386
00:28:27,385 --> 00:28:28,515
In a bad way?

387
00:28:29,215 --> 00:28:33,355
He's so famous these days. He's all over magazines and TV.

388
00:28:34,385 --> 00:28:36,455
I used to wonder what all the hype was about,

389
00:28:36,955 --> 00:28:38,225
but I think I'm starting to get it.

390
00:28:40,025 --> 00:28:43,165
So you have no plans to come back to this world for good?

391
00:28:44,235 --> 00:28:47,835
- Not a chance. - Why? You seem to be having fun.

392
00:28:49,175 --> 00:28:50,735
But it's not fulfilling.

393
00:28:51,305 --> 00:28:55,415
Even with a brilliant strategy, I don't feel better about myself.

394
00:28:58,915 --> 00:28:59,915
Hey, Shin Jae.

395
00:29:00,885 --> 00:29:04,115
The thing you mentioned last time about the foundation.

396
00:29:04,155 --> 00:29:05,755
Why didn't you marry my mom?

397
00:29:06,285 --> 00:29:07,785
I wanted a little brother or sister.

398
00:29:12,925 --> 00:29:14,395
Talk about coming out of left field.

399
00:29:15,095 --> 00:29:17,595
You come at me from every direction. How's a guy supposed to be ready?

400
00:29:17,995 --> 00:29:20,535
Let's not get into it today. I'm tired as it is.

401
00:29:21,435 --> 00:29:25,345
Please, just think it over. Until the next time we meet, okay?

402
00:29:37,815 --> 00:29:39,585
I just got home.

403
00:29:39,655 --> 00:29:42,255
Are you sure you're okay with Han Min Seo staying with you?

404
00:29:42,525 --> 00:29:43,955
I keep telling you I'm fine.

405
00:29:44,025 --> 00:29:47,765
Don't be too trusting. You barely know her.

406
00:29:47,825 --> 00:29:49,965
I know. Don't worry and get home safe.

407
00:29:51,695 --> 00:29:53,705
I've armed the security system at the front door,

408
00:29:53,765 --> 00:29:56,375
so if anything happens, I'll be notified immediately.

409
00:30:17,625 --> 00:30:18,665
Don't you have...

410
00:30:19,825 --> 00:30:20,825
any family?

411
00:30:22,695 --> 00:30:23,935
It's just me.

412
00:30:25,335 --> 00:30:26,965
Min Seo, you can use that room over there.

413
00:30:27,365 --> 00:30:30,175
My friends crash here sometimes, so there's already a bed.

414
00:30:31,105 --> 00:30:34,005
Let's have you take a break from your hotel job for a while.

415
00:30:34,205 --> 00:30:35,915
We don't know what those guys will try to pull.

416
00:30:37,075 --> 00:30:40,685
- Okay. - First, go ahead and unpack.

417
00:30:40,985 --> 00:30:42,615
Let me know if you need anything.

418
00:30:44,055 --> 00:30:45,055
Why...

419
00:30:47,985 --> 00:30:49,995
aren't you asking me to act as bait?

420
00:30:51,455 --> 00:30:55,435
If I just took one more job, then you guys could raid the place...

421
00:30:55,665 --> 00:30:57,135
or get your hands on a client's phone.

422
00:30:57,635 --> 00:30:59,005
That's the most surefire way to do this, isn't it?

423
00:31:03,175 --> 00:31:04,505
Don't you remember my promise?

424
00:31:04,975 --> 00:31:08,105
That I would make sure you wouldn't get hurt.

425
00:31:10,015 --> 00:31:13,145
Besides, that's not how we operate.

426
00:31:58,795 --> 00:32:00,165
(Connect In)

427
00:32:01,795 --> 00:32:02,795
(Connect In)

428
00:32:43,635 --> 00:32:44,705
(Hong Yeon Hui)

429
00:32:50,215 --> 00:32:51,475
Yes, this is Yoon Ra Young.

430
00:32:51,815 --> 00:32:53,615
So, about that DNA sample.

431
00:32:54,315 --> 00:32:56,385
You took care of it, right?

432
00:32:56,885 --> 00:32:59,585
It went through without any issues. Thank you.

433
00:33:00,625 --> 00:33:04,295
So what do you need me to do now? To get out of this hellhole?

434
00:33:05,965 --> 00:33:07,725
You need to map out that hell.

435
00:33:08,395 --> 00:33:10,335
Every single nook and cranny.

436
00:33:11,035 --> 00:33:12,065
And then what?

437
00:33:12,435 --> 00:33:13,635
We'll design it.

438
00:33:14,265 --> 00:33:16,605
A way to build an escape route out of there.

439
00:33:17,605 --> 00:33:18,675
I like the sound of that.

440
00:33:19,305 --> 00:33:21,775
I'll come see you when my map of hell is complete.

441
00:34:25,175 --> 00:34:28,945
So, about that DNA sample. You took care of it, right?

442
00:34:29,075 --> 00:34:31,645
It went through without any issues. Thank you.

443
00:34:36,415 --> 00:34:37,455
There. It's done.

444
00:34:38,185 --> 00:34:39,485
Just like you wanted.

445
00:34:50,795 --> 00:34:52,065
And the DNA results?

446
00:34:58,535 --> 00:35:00,844
Here's the cross-analysis of the DNA...

447
00:35:00,845 --> 00:35:02,105
Yoon Ra Young had me swap,

448
00:35:02,175 --> 00:35:06,445
and the suspect's bloodstain from the 2005 case.

449
00:35:08,485 --> 00:35:09,715
I deserve to know why.

450
00:35:10,215 --> 00:35:11,755
I'm your wife, after all.

451
00:35:13,985 --> 00:35:16,025
Why are you so obsessed with her?

452
00:35:22,895 --> 00:35:25,865
Don't cross the line. Just do what you're told.

453
00:35:26,165 --> 00:35:27,405
Keep your promise.

454
00:35:28,305 --> 00:35:29,935
Your promise to divorce me.

455
00:35:30,375 --> 00:35:33,475
Every word Yoon Ra Young says, every text she sends...

456
00:35:33,745 --> 00:35:35,815
Report it all to me, down to her very breath.

457
00:35:36,215 --> 00:35:37,545
Leave nothing out.

458
00:36:06,945 --> 00:36:09,815
(Mujin Police Station)

459
00:36:15,545 --> 00:36:17,085
(Welcome to Dike, Hankuk University's law society)

460
00:36:17,485 --> 00:36:19,555
A club from Hankuk University's College of Law?

461
00:36:19,655 --> 00:36:20,725
(Welcome to Dike, Hankuk University's law society)

462
00:36:23,755 --> 00:36:26,295
- Hey. This came for you. - Thanks.

463
00:36:29,435 --> 00:36:32,334
Hankuk University College of Law? Isn't that where your wife went?

464
00:36:32,335 --> 00:36:33,335
Right.

465
00:36:34,735 --> 00:36:36,675
You'd better treat her like a queen, man.

466
00:36:39,245 --> 00:36:41,075
- I'm out of here. - Later.

467
00:36:45,345 --> 00:36:46,384
("Went out for Air")

468
00:36:46,385 --> 00:36:47,385
("Hankuk Student Park Ju Hwan missing")

469
00:36:49,085 --> 00:36:50,415
("Hankuk Law Student Still Missing, Probe Stalled")

470
00:36:51,555 --> 00:36:53,485
("Hankuk Law Student Still Missing, Probe Stalled")

471
00:36:56,525 --> 00:36:58,655
("Hankuk Law Student Missing 2 Days Police Search Underway")

472
00:37:00,925 --> 00:37:03,095
Hankuk University College of Law academic society...

473
00:37:07,335 --> 00:37:10,035
(Lieutenant Gu Seon Kyu, Seoul Mujin Police Station)

474
00:37:53,545 --> 00:37:54,585
Min Seo.

475
00:37:56,385 --> 00:37:57,885
You're awake.

476
00:37:59,485 --> 00:38:01,255
There were only eggs in the fridge, so...

477
00:38:01,425 --> 00:38:04,325
I don't really cook at home...

478
00:38:04,625 --> 00:38:06,895
I didn't even think about it. You must be starving.

479
00:38:07,465 --> 00:38:08,465
By the way,

480
00:38:11,695 --> 00:38:13,365
why were you sleeping in the living room?

481
00:38:14,835 --> 00:38:19,005
It's just a habit. Don't mind me.

482
00:38:24,215 --> 00:38:25,785
I made some for you too.

483
00:38:26,385 --> 00:38:27,445
Would you like some?

484
00:38:33,355 --> 00:38:34,455
While you're staying here,

485
00:38:35,125 --> 00:38:38,225
I'll make sure you're taken care of at mealtimes.

486
00:38:39,965 --> 00:38:41,065
You don't have to do that.

487
00:38:41,625 --> 00:38:43,735
I'm used to it. I've lived on my own for a while.

488
00:38:49,035 --> 00:38:51,835
What about your parents?

489
00:38:54,175 --> 00:38:56,345
They passed away. Both of them.

490
00:38:59,915 --> 00:39:02,955
How did you end up working for Connect?

491
00:39:04,555 --> 00:39:06,055
I had a debt to pay off.

492
00:39:06,825 --> 00:39:08,785
And I'm still paying it off.

493
00:39:13,825 --> 00:39:18,595
Speaking of which, why don't you come work at our firm?

494
00:39:18,665 --> 00:39:19,665
Part-time.

495
00:39:20,705 --> 00:39:21,935
A part-time job?

496
00:39:22,935 --> 00:39:25,005
You can't go back to your hotel job for a while,

497
00:39:25,105 --> 00:39:27,545
and I'm not comfortable with you home alone.

498
00:39:27,605 --> 00:39:30,875
And as it happens, we were hiring someone anyway.

499
00:39:30,945 --> 00:39:33,745
You could also help us track Connect in your spare time.

500
00:39:34,315 --> 00:39:35,315
What do you think?

501
00:39:37,855 --> 00:39:39,015
Okay, I'll do it.

502
00:40:03,545 --> 00:40:05,544
Honey, what club were you in when you were in college?

503
00:40:05,545 --> 00:40:06,785
A club?

504
00:40:07,245 --> 00:40:08,745
Why the sudden interest?

505
00:40:09,315 --> 00:40:10,755
Just curious.

506
00:40:12,885 --> 00:40:14,125
It was just, you know,

507
00:40:14,885 --> 00:40:16,655
one of those academic clubs everyone joins.

508
00:40:19,265 --> 00:40:20,795
The academic society, Dike.

509
00:40:22,895 --> 00:40:25,765
What is this? Are you interrogating a suspect?

510
00:40:26,935 --> 00:40:29,135
And if I were, would you even answer me?

511
00:40:29,535 --> 00:40:32,405
- Honey. - This is what you always do.

512
00:40:33,345 --> 00:40:35,045
All I want from you is trust,

513
00:40:36,045 --> 00:40:37,745
but you just plead the fifth.

514
00:40:38,415 --> 00:40:41,945
No matter how much I worry or wonder about you,

515
00:40:42,115 --> 00:40:43,985
there's always something you're not telling me.

516
00:40:49,085 --> 00:40:50,455
Did I ever tell you?

517
00:40:51,095 --> 00:40:52,725
Why I became a cop?

518
00:40:53,725 --> 00:40:56,165
Back when my father had his accident,

519
00:40:56,795 --> 00:40:58,495
the police failed to catch who did it,

520
00:40:58,795 --> 00:41:00,205
so I made a decision right then and there.

521
00:41:00,805 --> 00:41:02,135
I knew I had to do it myself.

522
00:41:02,935 --> 00:41:04,905
If no one else was going to protect my family,

523
00:41:06,275 --> 00:41:07,605
then I'll have to be the one to do it.

524
00:41:11,145 --> 00:41:12,375
So you see, Hyun Jin,

525
00:41:13,885 --> 00:41:15,285
that man in a green hoodie...

526
00:41:16,155 --> 00:41:17,515
I'm definitely going to catch him.

527
00:41:35,335 --> 00:41:36,535
How can I help you?

528
00:41:39,205 --> 00:41:40,545
I'm Gu Seon Kyu.

529
00:41:42,075 --> 00:41:43,145
(Hankuk University)

530
00:41:43,215 --> 00:41:44,975
I'm looking into this case.

531
00:41:46,115 --> 00:41:48,985
They sent me to you from the law school.

532
00:41:52,755 --> 00:41:54,825
It was the day of our club's volunteer event.

533
00:41:55,555 --> 00:41:58,155
We had a small get-together after the event,

534
00:41:58,825 --> 00:42:00,425
and at some point, Ju Hwan disappeared.

535
00:42:01,195 --> 00:42:03,635
We all split up to look for him.

536
00:42:05,095 --> 00:42:09,005
That's all I know. It's what I told the police at the time.

537
00:42:09,635 --> 00:42:11,405
As for what happened after that,

538
00:42:12,805 --> 00:42:14,305
I have absolutely no idea.

539
00:42:14,945 --> 00:42:16,715
I have one more question for you.

540
00:42:18,275 --> 00:42:21,215
Do you happen to know anything about this stamp?

541
00:42:26,255 --> 00:42:27,355
Let me see.

542
00:42:33,195 --> 00:42:36,435
This is the stamp our club used to use.

543
00:42:37,035 --> 00:42:38,495
When the university transitioned to a law school system,

544
00:42:38,795 --> 00:42:42,265
the club closed, and since I stayed, I somehow ended up keeping it.

545
00:42:43,135 --> 00:42:44,135
I see.

546
00:42:45,135 --> 00:42:46,845
Thank you for your time.

547
00:42:49,205 --> 00:42:50,275
Excuse me,

548
00:42:51,245 --> 00:42:52,915
but may I ask what this is all about?

549
00:42:53,015 --> 00:42:57,585
I can't discuss an active case. I hope you understand.

550
00:42:58,855 --> 00:42:59,925
Of course.

551
00:43:00,625 --> 00:43:01,725
(Call detail records)

552
00:43:01,785 --> 00:43:03,295
(Seohan Bank transaction history: Nam Jong Min)

553
00:43:05,295 --> 00:43:08,265
His financial records and call logs...

554
00:43:08,525 --> 00:43:09,665
are all clean.

555
00:43:09,935 --> 00:43:12,665
So no record of any suspicious contact.

556
00:43:13,365 --> 00:43:14,635
He's probably a Connector.

557
00:43:14,905 --> 00:43:15,905
Right.

558
00:43:17,675 --> 00:43:20,175
Then what's the chance Nam Jong Min himself is Green Hoodie?

559
00:43:20,245 --> 00:43:24,315
The day Attorney Yoon was attacked and your car was vandalized,

560
00:43:24,575 --> 00:43:27,085
Nam Jong Min has a solid alibi for both incidents.

561
00:43:27,415 --> 00:43:30,385
We confirmed he was in his lab at the university at the time.

562
00:43:33,355 --> 00:43:35,755
I left this out of the report because it seemed minor, but...

563
00:43:40,565 --> 00:43:41,725
Professor Nam Jong Min...

564
00:43:42,195 --> 00:43:45,695
donates to a private organization called Sunshine since 2005.

565
00:43:45,995 --> 00:43:49,975
- Sunshine? - It helps sexual assault survivors.

566
00:44:39,685 --> 00:44:42,185
So that flash drive was real.

567
00:44:43,495 --> 00:44:46,425
If it's not Nam Jong Min, then who is it?

568
00:44:50,635 --> 00:44:53,035
You can just organize the files by case number.

569
00:44:53,205 --> 00:44:56,005
When you're finished, just put them in our cabinet.

570
00:44:56,475 --> 00:45:01,045
You can serve guests refreshments. The break room is right here.

571
00:45:01,575 --> 00:45:03,745
If we need any supplies, just write them down.

572
00:45:06,485 --> 00:45:08,845
What's that room over there?

573
00:45:18,925 --> 00:45:20,665
This is a space just for the three of us.

574
00:45:21,525 --> 00:45:25,135
We keep some of our more sensitive case files in here.

575
00:45:26,235 --> 00:45:28,335
So it's like a secure area.

576
00:45:29,935 --> 00:45:30,975
At first,

577
00:45:31,505 --> 00:45:32,875
it was made because of me.

578
00:45:33,275 --> 00:45:37,645
There are times when I need a place where I know I'm truly safe.

579
00:45:38,015 --> 00:45:39,845
A place where I can feel at ease.

580
00:45:40,215 --> 00:45:42,845
Even if I'm not physically in here, just knowing it's here helps.

581
00:45:45,085 --> 00:45:46,155
Attorney Yoon.

582
00:45:48,985 --> 00:45:52,025
- Hey! What brings you here? - It's been a while.

583
00:45:52,625 --> 00:45:54,625
So, is everyone managing to stay off the cigarettes?

584
00:45:55,365 --> 00:45:56,865
These have to be better for you than nicotine.

585
00:45:59,395 --> 00:46:02,065
But you can't have these unless you line up before opening.

586
00:46:02,435 --> 00:46:04,135
I've tried and failed twice!

587
00:46:05,235 --> 00:46:07,005
Oh, gosh.

588
00:46:07,445 --> 00:46:09,875
- Should I get on my knees and bow? - Come on. Don't be dramatic.

589
00:46:10,915 --> 00:46:12,575
Shin Jae, can I talk to you for a minute?

590
00:46:13,045 --> 00:46:14,645
Sure. Let's go to that room.

591
00:46:14,985 --> 00:46:16,984
Ra Young, could you tell them to serve us two teas?

592
00:46:16,985 --> 00:46:18,085
Sure.

593
00:46:19,015 --> 00:46:20,825
- This way. - Look at this.

594
00:46:22,655 --> 00:46:24,895
What was it you said to me last time?

595
00:46:26,395 --> 00:46:29,425
Something about why I never married your mother?

596
00:46:31,965 --> 00:46:33,405
I've always wondered about that.

597
00:46:35,205 --> 00:46:36,205
Because...

598
00:46:36,635 --> 00:46:39,475
your mother and I never had that kind of relationship.

599
00:46:39,575 --> 00:46:41,945
Really? After all this time?

600
00:46:42,345 --> 00:46:43,475
Not even once.

601
00:46:45,215 --> 00:46:49,445
But your mother was always the greatest partner I ever had.

602
00:46:49,885 --> 00:46:53,685
CEO Seong and I have always been on the same page.

603
00:46:55,925 --> 00:46:59,525
So you're rejecting my proposal, then.

604
00:47:01,095 --> 00:47:02,725
But just this one time,

605
00:47:03,095 --> 00:47:05,395
I'm going to paint a different picture than CEO Seong.

606
00:47:09,135 --> 00:47:11,035
(Managing Partner Kang Shin Jae)

607
00:47:18,745 --> 00:47:20,785
(Letter of Resignation)

608
00:47:20,815 --> 00:47:22,785
From the executives, including myself,

609
00:47:23,315 --> 00:47:25,015
and 50 of our senior staff. These are our resignations.

610
00:47:25,415 --> 00:47:27,155
They're the current backbone of Haeil.

611
00:47:27,785 --> 00:47:29,925
If every single one of us leaves Haeil at once...

612
00:47:29,995 --> 00:47:31,425
Haeil would be crippled.

613
00:47:32,125 --> 00:47:35,565
Its collected data and connections. That's the source of Haeil's power.

614
00:47:36,595 --> 00:47:40,205
We'll use this as leverage on CEO Seong's succession plan.

615
00:47:40,265 --> 00:47:44,375
Once the successor spot is vacant, incorporation will be inevitable.

616
00:47:44,735 --> 00:47:47,005
And the first order of business for the Haeil Law Corporation...

617
00:47:47,505 --> 00:47:50,845
- will create a public foundation. - Then, the new head of Haeil...

618
00:47:51,575 --> 00:47:52,875
will be you.

619
00:47:53,915 --> 00:47:55,145
I'll be the wind in your sails.

620
00:47:55,785 --> 00:47:57,155
Ride the swing that I'm pushing for you,

621
00:47:57,485 --> 00:48:00,525
and go as high as you can. To wherever you want to go.

622
00:48:13,605 --> 00:48:15,165
(Managing Partner Kang Shin Jae)

623
00:48:15,835 --> 00:48:17,275
Thank you very much.

624
00:48:41,565 --> 00:48:43,695
- Min Seo. - What is it?

625
00:48:48,635 --> 00:48:50,105
I saw the VIP.

626
00:48:51,805 --> 00:48:52,805
The user from Connect.

627
00:48:55,545 --> 00:48:58,545
Who exactly are you talking about?

628
00:48:59,745 --> 00:49:01,345
The man who's in that room right now.

629
00:49:04,455 --> 00:49:05,485
Don't tell me...

630
00:49:07,185 --> 00:49:10,755
- You mean Attorney Kwon? - That's ridiculous.

631
00:49:11,825 --> 00:49:12,995
There's no way...

632
00:49:15,665 --> 00:49:17,665
Min Seo, are you sure you're not mistaken?

633
00:49:19,295 --> 00:49:21,205
He was wearing the exact same ring.

634
00:49:25,875 --> 00:49:27,145
I remember his face too.

635
00:49:29,405 --> 00:49:30,945
He was there.

636
00:49:32,175 --> 00:49:33,245
He was into...

637
00:49:33,785 --> 00:49:34,985
a younger man.

638
00:49:42,685 --> 00:49:44,955
(Hankuk University College of Law Newsletter)

639
00:49:51,295 --> 00:49:52,295
(2005 Hankuk University College of Law)

640
00:49:56,575 --> 00:49:58,975
The law school club, Dike.

641
00:50:01,775 --> 00:50:02,775
The back of my hand?

642
00:50:06,275 --> 00:50:07,415
("Went out for Air")

643
00:50:07,485 --> 00:50:09,215
("Hankuk Student Park Ju Hwan missing")

644
00:50:22,465 --> 00:50:24,435
- Hello? - Just listen.

645
00:50:24,935 --> 00:50:27,065
Min Seo says she's seen Attorney Kwon before.

646
00:50:27,605 --> 00:50:28,835
As a Connect user.

647
00:50:30,635 --> 00:50:31,875
Are you sure?

648
00:50:32,035 --> 00:50:35,045
I need his cell phone. Can you check it for me?

649
00:50:39,675 --> 00:50:40,785
Hang on.

650
00:51:03,335 --> 00:51:05,035
Shin Jae, are you okay?

651
00:51:05,775 --> 00:51:06,775
Let me see.

652
00:51:07,045 --> 00:51:09,375
Please take me to the hospital. Quickly.

653
00:51:09,445 --> 00:51:10,445
Hey, let's go. Quick.

654
00:51:11,775 --> 00:51:13,945
(CEO's office)

655
00:51:14,085 --> 00:51:15,215
What happened?

656
00:51:15,745 --> 00:51:17,415
Take care of things in the room for me.

657
00:51:17,915 --> 00:51:18,915
Let's go.

658
00:51:44,145 --> 00:51:46,375
(Connect In)

659
00:51:52,855 --> 00:51:53,985
Oh, my gosh.

660
00:51:55,355 --> 00:51:56,755
(Connect In)

661
00:52:02,865 --> 00:52:05,265
(Warning: Critical security threat detected)

662
00:52:24,615 --> 00:52:25,685
This one's better.

663
00:52:33,125 --> 00:52:36,325
Will it take long? Shin Jae will be back any minute.

664
00:52:38,535 --> 00:52:40,205
(Connect In)

665
00:52:40,465 --> 00:52:42,265
- I'll keep a lookout. - Okay.

666
00:52:48,675 --> 00:52:50,045
(Connect In)

667
00:52:51,345 --> 00:52:52,345
I'm in.

668
00:52:52,815 --> 00:52:53,815
You unlocked it?

669
00:52:59,785 --> 00:53:00,925
This is it.

670
00:53:01,985 --> 00:53:03,155
It was true.

671
00:53:04,625 --> 00:53:05,625
(Deleting app)

672
00:53:06,495 --> 00:53:07,495
What's wrong with this thing?

673
00:53:10,965 --> 00:53:11,965
(Deleting app)

674
00:53:14,235 --> 00:53:15,335
(Deleting app)

675
00:53:16,405 --> 00:53:18,375
(Deletion complete)

676
00:53:20,075 --> 00:53:21,205
What just happened?

677
00:53:21,745 --> 00:53:25,645
- It's gone from my phone too. - Hey, did you mess something up?

678
00:53:25,815 --> 00:53:28,285
No, it wasn't me. They wiped it remotely.

679
00:53:29,245 --> 00:53:30,855
They've been watching us this whole time.

680
00:53:31,285 --> 00:53:33,015
We were the ones being hacked.

681
00:53:40,625 --> 00:53:42,025
And what about the message card?

682
00:53:56,815 --> 00:53:57,875
Thanks.

683
00:53:58,645 --> 00:53:59,975
Thank you.

684
00:54:07,685 --> 00:54:11,525
(Hankuk University College of Law Newsletter)

685
00:54:15,925 --> 00:54:17,665
(Winners, the 3rd mock trial and best advocate)

686
00:54:17,735 --> 00:54:19,665
(2005 law school club: Dike)

687
00:54:28,975 --> 00:54:32,775
(Dike)

688
00:54:34,785 --> 00:54:36,015
(Dike)

689
00:54:36,085 --> 00:54:37,085
(2005 law school club: Dike)

690
00:54:40,125 --> 00:54:42,055
(College of Law: Yoon Ra Young, Kang Shin Jae)

691
00:54:42,125 --> 00:54:44,625
(Hwang Hyun Jin, Park Ju Hwan)

692
00:54:50,835 --> 00:54:53,265
("Went out for Air")

693
00:54:53,335 --> 00:54:55,335
("Hankuk Student Park Ju Hwan missing")

694
00:54:57,835 --> 00:55:00,345
(2005 law school club: Dike)

695
00:55:01,745 --> 00:55:03,275
Park Ju Hwan.

696
00:55:03,545 --> 00:55:05,345
(Park Ju Hwan, Hwang Hyun Jin)

697
00:55:05,415 --> 00:55:07,345
(Yoon Ra Young, Kang Shin Jae)

698
00:55:07,415 --> 00:55:09,445
(From left, counter-clockwise)

699
00:55:09,515 --> 00:55:11,855
(College of Law: Yoon Ra Young, Kang Shin Jae)

700
00:55:11,915 --> 00:55:14,155
(Hwang Hyun Jin, Park Ju Hwan)

701
00:55:16,085 --> 00:55:17,454
The person you called is unavailable.

702
00:55:17,455 --> 00:55:18,895
Leave a message after the tone.

703
00:55:21,565 --> 00:55:23,264
Where are you? Call me.

704
00:55:23,265 --> 00:55:24,295
(Shin Jae)

705
00:55:31,735 --> 00:55:34,505
- Shin Jae? - Attorney Yoon is here.

706
00:55:34,805 --> 00:55:36,815
Attorney Yoon, he says he's a friend of yours.

707
00:56:56,255 --> 00:56:59,125
It's been a while. I missed you, Ra Young.

708
00:57:08,465 --> 00:57:10,105
("Hankuk Student Park Ju Hwan missing")

709
00:57:20,415 --> 00:57:23,385
(From an old friend, Park Ju Hwan)

710
00:57:23,445 --> 00:57:24,515
(College of Law: Yoon Ra Young, Kang Shin Jae)

711
00:57:24,585 --> 00:57:25,715
(Hwang Hyun Jin, Park Ju Hwan)

712
00:57:25,785 --> 00:57:28,355
(From an old friend, Park Ju Hwan)

713
00:57:30,955 --> 00:57:34,865
(Honour)

714
00:58:26,475 --> 00:58:29,215
What if Park Je Yeol really goes public with it?

715
00:58:29,515 --> 00:58:30,915
We'll lose everything.

716
00:58:32,715 --> 00:58:35,225
If you keep this up, Yoon Ra Young is the one who's going to get hurt.

717
00:58:35,555 --> 00:58:38,155
- So you remember now. - And I have the proof.

718
00:58:38,355 --> 00:58:40,995
He had three priors, and they suspended the indictment?

719
00:58:41,065 --> 00:58:44,195
If this gets out, Hyun Jin is in the most danger.

720
00:58:44,295 --> 00:58:47,905
How will he react when he finds out his wife's an attempted murderer?

721
00:58:48,105 --> 00:58:49,465
Was this your doing, Mom?

722
00:58:49,905 --> 00:58:53,135
We're going to strike first. That way, they can't say a thing.
